  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Evaluation of efficacy and safety from 6hours of 7 cmH2O CPAP after weaning in patients
      undergoing lung resection, on the prevention of atelectasis / pneumonia and gas exchange
      improve.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Multicenter randomized clinical trial. 460 patients randomly assigned to treatment and
      control groups will be studied. The main variables are the frequency of atelectasis or
      pneumonia, defined by clinical and radiological criteria, the FiO2/PaO2 ratio, 7 and 24 h
      after weaning, and hospital stay.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
