  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Undergoing thoracic surgery including resection of lung parenchyma.

          -  To have given signed consent to enter in the study.

        Exclusion Criteria:

        Weaning in the first 4h after the intervention end.

          -  Suspected bronchopleural fistula at the admission to the surgical ICU.

          -  Patients with facial problems or a history of intolerance to CPAP masks.

          -  Having significant bullous emphysema defined as the presence of more than 5 contiguous
             bullae &lt;2cm or the existence of a pulmonary bulla&gt; 2 cm or dystrophy bullosa, not in
             the area to dry and having had a previous pneumothorax.

          -  Known Obstructive Apnea Hypopnea syndrome known or some form of noninvasive
             ventilation prescribed.

          -  Immunocompromised patients, or having used an immunosuppressor drug at least one month
             prior to surgery with potential (except corticosteroids administered by inhalation)
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
